The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bihar firms in red: CAG
                                                                                                               Bihar firms in red: CAG
                            
	Patna, July 15 (PTI): Several state-run companies and statutory corporations in Bihar have incurred huge losses, successively, and are now in red, stated a Comptroller and Auditor-General of India (CAG) report.        
	CAGs report for the period that ended on March 31, 2008, calculated 54 public sector undertakings  50 government companies and four statutory corporations  in Bihar.         
	It stated six working PSUs earned an aggregate profit of Rs 38.24 crore. Against this, 13 working PSUs incurred an aggregate loss of Rs 946.16 crore. Seven working firms accumulated losses worth Rs 226.55 crore.                                                                                                                                                                            
